#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Kosiyavagga"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs0.5"
msgid ""
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "13. Dvebhāgasikkhāpada"
msgstr "13. The training rule on two parts"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.13.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2121"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ "
"suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpetun”ti, te thokaññeva odātaṃ "
"ante ādiyitvā tatheva suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpenti."
msgstr ""
"At that time, when the monks from the group of six knew that the Master had "
"prohibited getting blankets made entirely of black wool, they added just a "
"little bit of white on the edge. In this way they got blankets made entirely "
"of black wool."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū thokaññeva odātaṃ ante ādiyitvā tatheva "
"suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six act like this?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2122"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.7"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, thokaññeva odātaṃ ante ādiyitvā tatheva "
"suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, thokaññeva odātaṃ ante ādiyitvā tatheva "
"suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you add just a little bit of white on the edge and in "
"this way get blankets made entirely of black wool?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.12a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2123"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.13"
msgid ""
"“Navaṃ pana bhikkhunā santhataṃ kārayamānena dve bhāgā suddhakāḷakānaṃ "
"eḷakalomānaṃ ādātabbā tatiyaṃ odātānaṃ catutthaṃ gocariyānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk is getting a new blanket made, he should use two parts of "
"entirely black wool, a third part of white, and a fourth part of brown."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.77"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs1.14"
msgid ""
"Anādā ce bhikkhu dve bhāge suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ tatiyaṃ odātānaṃ "
"catutthaṃ gocariyānaṃ navaṃ santhataṃ kārāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"If he gets a new blanket made without using two parts of entirely black "
"wool, a third part of white, and a fourth part of brown, he commits an "
"offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-c1.15"
msgid "(<em>13</em>:<strong>32</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.13.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2124"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Navaṃ nāma"
msgstr "New:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "karaṇaṃ upādāya vuccati."
msgstr "newly made is what is meant."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2125"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Santhataṃ nāma"
msgstr "A blanket:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "santharitvā kataṃ hoti avāyimaṃ."
msgstr "it is made by spreading out, not by weaving."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2126"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "Kārayamānenāti"
msgstr "Getting made:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "karonto vā kārāpento vā."
msgstr "making or getting made."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2127"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Dve bhāgā suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ ādātabbāti"
msgstr "He should use two parts of entirely black wool:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "dhārayitvā dve tulā ādātabbā."
msgstr "having weighed it, he should use two measures."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2128"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ odātānanti"
msgstr "A third part of white:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "tulaṃ odātānaṃ."
msgstr "one measure of white."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Catutthaṃ gocariyānanti"
msgstr "A fourth part of brown:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "tulaṃ gocariyānaṃ."
msgstr "one measure of brown."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.227"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2130"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.13"
msgid ""
"Anādā ce bhikkhu dve bhāge suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ tatiyaṃ odātānaṃ "
"catutthaṃ gocariyānanti."
msgstr ""
"Without using two parts of entirely black wool, a third part of white, and a "
"fourth part of brown:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.14"
msgid ""
"Anādiyitvā dve tule suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ tulaṃ odātānaṃ tulaṃ "
"gocariyānaṃ navaṃ santhataṃ karoti vā kārāpeti vā payoge dukkaṭaṃ,"
msgstr ""
"for the act of making it, or getting it made, without using two measures of "
"entirely black wool, one measure of white, and one measure of brown, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the blanket, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr ""
"The blanket should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.19"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, santhataṃ anādiyitvā dve tule suddhakāḷakānaṃ eḷakalomānaṃ "
"tulaṃ odātānaṃ tulaṃ gocariyānaṃ kārāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this blanket which I got made without using two measures of "
"entirely black wool, one measure of white, and one measure of brown, is to "
"be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this blanket back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.23a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2131"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.24"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.25"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he gets others to finish what he began himself, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.26"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.27"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he gets others to finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2132"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he makes one, or gets one made, for someone else, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.29"
msgid "Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he obtains one that was made by someone else and then uses it, he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2133"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.30"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.31"
msgid "tulaṃ odātānaṃ tulaṃ gocariyānaṃ ādiyitvā karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes one using one measure of white and one measure of brown;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.78"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.32"
msgid "bahutaraṃ odātānaṃ bahutaraṃ gocariyānaṃ ādiyitvā karoti,"
msgstr ""
"if he makes on using more than one measure of white and more than one "
"measure of brown;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.33"
msgid "suddhaṃ odātānaṃ suddhaṃ gocariyānaṃ ādiyitvā karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes one using just white and just brown;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.34"
msgid ""
"vitānaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā sāṇipākāraṃ vā bhisiṃ vā bibbohanaṃ vā karoti,"
msgstr ""
"if he makes a canopy, a floor cover, a screen-wall, a mattress, or a pillow;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.35"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.36"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2134"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np13:pts-cs2.37"
msgid "Dvebhāgasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr "The third rule, the training rule on two parts, is finished."

